data.description: Opportunity knocks. Small acreage in northern Johnson County, Kansas soon to be part of comprehensive redevelopment.  Currently zoned R-1 with single family home required to be listed as residential property.  However, the City of Merriam has already designated property as future planned commercial zoning and priced accordingly. The Merriam Connected Corridor Study conceptualizes redevelopment of Merriam Dr. as it progresses through Merriam, Mission, northern Overland Park, and Kansas City.  This is just under one full acre of land and will be a part of historic Merriam Comprehensive Redevelopment Plan. Frontage on 55th St. designated as major east/west arterial collector. Property is located at the corner of Merriam Dr. with close access to I-35, Johnson Dr., and Shawnee Mission Pkwy.  Property overlaps Downtown Merriam Redevelopment Plan with the Merriam Connected Corridor Plan. Don't miss the opportunity to be part of this Historic Redevelopment that will redefine northern Johnson County.
